==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skirl
<hw>Skirl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[Of Scand.
origin, and originally the same word as E. <ets>shrill</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To utter in a shrill tone; to scream.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skirl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skirl
<hw>Skirl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrill cry or sound.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skirlcock</ent>⟦br⟧
